{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.11 result-free command-10 bootstrap/inventory rehearsal reached no producer or outcome but PyTorch 2.9 emitted a TF32 deprecation warning on stderr through legacy precision access. Its sealed exact-zero-stderr contract therefore makes v1.11 terminal; v1.12 uses fresh namespaces and does not repair, resume, relabel, or reuse that attempt."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.12 prebinding runtime identity binds an exact five-field string hierarchy: global_fp32_precision, cudnn_fp32_precision, cudnn_conv_fp32_precision, cudnn_rnn_fp32_precision, and cuda_matmul_fp32_precision. Active implementation code contains no legacy allow_tf32 getter, setter, attribute, or global float32-matmul-precision API access."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Determinism explicitly selects ieee for CUDA matmul, cuDNN convolution, and cuDNN RNN. Independent CEM replay snapshots and restores all three operator leaves independently in a finally path, including successful and forced-failure exits, while warning-as-error and semantic precision tests cover the migration."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Nested zero-stderr enforcement is end to end: the source-mode generator rejects any nonempty path-mode or descriptor-mode child stderr; central and independent consumers require the empty-stream SHA-256, zero bytes, and empty payload on every repeated prebinding and restart row; and launch replay must equal the bound zero-stderr command-10 evidence."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The changed representations are versioned and propagated consistently: prebinding requests and reports use prospect.wm001.prebinding-conformance-request.v2 and prospect.wm001.prebinding-conformance.v2, and the preformal report and generation envelope use v2. The formal/raw protocol schemas remain v9 and unchanged v1 receipt representations remain v1 rather than being relabeled."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Lineage directly supersedes the sealed v1.11 protocol digest and derives fresh v1.12 masters and streams in a new canonical domain. Verification accounts for 10 current masters and 1,360 current streams against 110 prior masters and 14,960 prior streams, with all master, stream, cross-master, and cross-stream collision classes empty."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The bound adversarial tests cover forbidden legacy precision APIs, warnings promoted to errors, exact IEEE leaf semantics, independent CEM restoration on success and failure, nested stderr injection, command-10 identity mutation, v2 schema rejection, lineage and seed arithmetic, recorded-versus-live consumer separation, and QA/runtime inventory inequality."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Scientific continuity is preserved: the four scientific top-level blocks reproduce SHA-256 fa44fd93a672db3905d45a0e99c568985e7e2e5d02d32043c830db413005a5c3, the four kernel source hashes remain unchanged, and the model, learning algorithm, optimizer, planner, controller, budgets, controls, metrics, thresholds, exclusions, and killing gates are not altered by this migration."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The execution closure uses fresh v1.12 QA and runtime environments installed non-editably from one reviewed wheel. Their Prospect version and distribution digest are identical, their package inventories are intentionally unequal because pytest, ruff, and mypy are QA-only, and the untouched runtime's exact 45-row installed closure verifies against requirements-wm001.lock."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"Command 10 is an exact result-free stop/go gate with separate stdout and stderr capture, sealed runtime launch, zero return, canonical passed output, and byte-empty stderr required before development. Shell invocation correction is permitted only before any sealed rehearsal process launches; once launched, refusal, nonzero return, or nonempty stderr is terminal and the command may not be repeated."},{"id":"F011","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The assurance boundary is stated negatively and without overclaim: tamper_resistant and external_attestation are false; repository, environment, result-path, filesystem, base-interpreter, and kernel integrity plus exclusive path use are trusted; hashes and cooperative locks do not defeat same-principal, privileged, compromised-kernel, or transient mutate-and-restore attacks."},{"id":"F012","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The canonical prospective manifest binds 86 live operative source, test, schema, seal, lock, build, plan, and runbook files by path, byte count, and SHA-256; the self-referential review file is intentionally outside that implementation manifest."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1638,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"4f2492932e1ab686f2446be8ec2a49dfdedf348b5b9aa63ba506e470a34feb63"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"